                    <div class="exc-description">
                        <p>As far as old-school exercises go, the barbell pullover has been around since resistance training first began. At its core, it involves bringing a weighted barbell over your head and back up again while lying on a bench. Alongside being easy to perform, it offers several useful benefits which will be described below.</p><p>Despite its versatility, it is less commonly used by most gym populations. To bring it back into the mainstream gym routines, weâ€™ve discussed everything about why it's so good. We detail the correct form, programming tips, suitable populations, and benefits below.</p>                    </div>
